headline: CrowdStrike earnings narrowly beat Wall Street's expectations
summary: CrowdStrike (CRWD) released third quarter results that came in roughly in line with expectations on the top and bottom lines. Third quarter revenue came in at $1.23 billion, narrowly beating estimates of $1.21 billion, while earnings per share (EPS) came in at $0.96, compared to $0.94 expected. The company lifted its full-year outlook and issued a slightly stronger-than-expected fourth quarter earnings guidance.
